Associate Engr Matl Process/Crystal Growth Engineer

Northrop Grumman

- Charlotte, NC 28273 (Olde Whitehall area)

Responsibilities:
Function as Process Owner supporting production of assigned crystal growth processes with data collection, process control, designed experiments, process documentation and operator training
Monitor/analyze process data, and growing crystal daily
Report/communicate crystal growth status with downstream departments and management team
Analyze and report failure mode and customer return to incorporate new learning and recommend/implement corrective actions
Perform hands-on work and work with operators in trouble-shooting process and equipment issues
Evaluate existing crystal growth methods, processes and sequences to optimize operation efficiency, including:
raw material processing
crystal growth control variables
crystal growth equipment
Lead projects with lean manufacturing concepts and report progress/issues/deliverablesin a timely manner
Work collaboratively with operators and engineers to manage changes to functionality for improved reliability, control, automation and safety
Propose/lead projects with scientific method to solve challenging crystal growth issues
RequiredQualifications:
BS in Physics, Chemistry, Chemical Engineering, Material Science and Engineering
Five years of manufacturing experience

Preferred Qualifications:
MS/PhD
Familiarity with electro-mechanical controlsystems, PID controls and loops, motors, motor drives
Crystal Growth experience
Familiarity withmaterials science/ceramics processing and the ability to understand drawings, in order to build, modify and troubleshoot electro-mechanical and controls equipment
